President Joe Biden visited the Port of Ponce in Puerto Rico to assess the damage caused by Hurricane Fiona and offer support to the affected communities. He expressed his commitment to helping Puerto Rico rebuild in a resilient way to withstand future storms. President Biden announced over $60 million in funding to help coastal areas become better prepared for future storms and highlighted the infrastructure investments already underway in Puerto Rico. He emphasized the importance of improving the power grid and ensuring clean, reliable, and affordable energy for the island. President Biden reassured the people of Puerto Rico that his administration is committed to standing with them and providing assistance for as long as it takes.